items.base_ground_truth_text: for the first canoe to come alongside there was an exclama-
tion of pity and wonder from the passengers as they looked
apparently quite contented, close to the faggots and burn-
ing embers placed on the stones which served as ballast.
holding up a couple of otter skins, and asking for largesse,
recognise the Yamaschoona! yamaschoona! which Dar-
win speaks of as Fuegian for Give me! give me!
